  section#runner-object
    h2 The Runner Object
    p.
      The Runner Object is a large, full-width section with padding on all four sides.
      It can be used for headers, footers, heros, highlight blocks, etc.,
      really, anything that looks like a “row” of a page.
      Change the window size and watch what happens to the padding.
    figure.docs-figure
      div.o-Runner
        h1 runner heading
        p runner content
      pre.docs-pre.
        &lt;div class="#[u o-Runner]"&gt;
          &lt;h1&gt;runner heading&lt;/h1&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;runner content&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    p Subclasses of the Runner Object simply vary the padding.
    p.
      Use #[code.docs-code .o-Runner--pageHeader] for headers of pages,
      whether they be generic pages or special pages with hero banner headers.
    figure.docs-figure
      div.o-Runner.o-Runner--pageHeader
        h1.o-Runner--pageHeader__Hn page heading
      pre.docs-pre.
        &lt;div class="#[u o-Runner]  #[u o-Runner--pageHeader]"&gt;
          &lt;h1&gt;page heading&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    p Use #[code.docs-code .o-Runner--highlight] for highlighted content callouts.
    figure.docs-figure
      div.o-Runner.o-Runner--highlight
        h1 highlight block heading
        p highlight content
      pre.docs-pre.
        &lt;div class="#[u o-Runner]  #[u o-Runner--highlight]"&gt;
          &lt;h1&gt;highlight block heading&lt;/h1&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;highlight content&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    p.
      Use #[code.docs-code .o-Runner--wrappedInner] if you want to override the normal behavior and
      remove all padding on x-small screens. This will make the inner #[code.docs-code :only-child]
      cover the entire Runner.
      Combine with other subclasses if necessary.
    figure.docs-figure
      aside.o-Runner.o-Runner--wrappedInner
        div
          h1 runner with inner wrapper
          p runner content
      pre.docs-pre.
        &lt;div class="#[u o-Runner]  #[u o-Runner--wrappedInner]"&gt;
          #[u &lt;div&gt;]
            &lt;h1&gt;Wrapper&lt;/h1&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;runner content&lt;/p&gt;
          #[u!= '&lt;/div&gt;']
        &lt;/div&gt;
  section#content-wrapper
    h2 The Content Wrapper
    p.
      This object wraps content, limiting its maximum width.
      Use it to wrap content directly inside a Runner
      (though it may not necessarily be a child of Runner).
    figure.docs-figure
      div.o-Runner
        div.o-ContentWrapper
          h1 content heading
          p content
      pre.docs-pre.
        &lt;div class="#[u o-Runner]"&gt;
          &lt;div class="#[u o-ContentWrapper]"&gt;
            &lt;h1&gt;content heading&lt;/h1&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;content&lt;/p&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
